<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41037c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41037c">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41037c"> 37(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> had issue</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">If, however, the husband <mark>had issue</mark> by the wife who could inherit the property as her heir, on the death of the wife, the husband became entitled to her property for the rest of his life, in priority to the wife&apos;s heir or other person entitled; such estate was known as an estate &ldquo;by the curtesy.&rdquo; <small> Maud I. Crofts, <a name="MICW" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#MICW"><cite title="source">Women under English Law</cite></a>, 1st ed. (1925) 33</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
